title: ANCYL: Urgent application to stop congress will be heard at 4pm
text:
Johannesburg - North West ANC Youth League member Thabo Molamu confirmed that an urgent application seeking to stop the leagueâ€™s congress from going ahead on Friday, would be heard at 16:00 on Thursday.
The matter is expected to be heard at the High Court in Pretoria.
Molamu, and several other ANC Youth League members in the North West, are believed to have turned to the court after "exhausting all internal processes".
The group alleges that there are unresolved disputes relating to the exclusion of delegates.
